TITLE: Defining Compaction Event Structures for LSM Management
DESCRIPTION: Implements the CompactionEvent and Label structs that represent table modifications during LSM tree compaction. These structures track the insertion, update, and removal of tables across different levels of the LSM tree.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tigerbeetle/tigerbeetle/blob/main/docs/internals/data_file.md#2025-04-14_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: zig
CODE:
```
const CompactionEvent = struct {
    label: Label
    table: TableInfo, // points to table's index block
};

const Label = struct {
    level: u6,
    event: enum(u2) { insert, update, remove },
};
```

